According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Military Intelligence, Surveillance & Reconnaissance (ISR) Market was valued at USD 44.4 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 46.9 billion in 2026 to USD 76.5 billion by 2035, registering a CAGR of 5.6% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing sustained growth as governments worldwide continue to strengthen national security capabilities amid rising geopolitical tensions, increasing defense expenditures, and rapid technological advancements. Modern ISR systems have become indispensable for military operations by providing real-time intelligence, enhancing situational awareness, and enabling faster, data-driven decision-making across land, air, sea, space, and cyber domains.
